# Forge Deployment Examples

## **Solo Developer (1 Person, 0€)**
- **Zweck**: Persönliches Tool (z.B. Code-Review-Agent)
- **Setup**: Local OpenClaw + PostgreSQL (Docker)
- **Tiers**: Tier 1 nur (10 REP)
- **Deployment**: `python genesis-agent.py` (Sepolia Testnet)
- **Skalierung**: 1-5 Agents, 0 L3

## **Small Team (2-10, 50€/Monat)**
- **Zweck**: Open-Source-Projekt (z.B. CRM-Plugin)
- **Infra**: Hetzner 2€ Node + Optimism L2
- **Tiers**: 0-2 (GitHub Oracle für REP)
- **Agents**: Contributor, Reviewer, Monitor
- **M2M**: Compute trades (Tier 1: €100 limit)

## **Startup/Team (10-50, 200€/Monat)**
- **Zweck**: SaaS (z.B. IoT-Dashboard)
- **Infra**: DigitalOcean K8s + L2
- **Tiers**: Voll (Killswitch Tier 3)
- **Deployment**: Terraform + CI/CD
- **Features**: Prediction Markets, ZK Privacy

## **Enterprise (50-500, 2k€/Monat)**
- **Zweck**: CRM/ERP/IoT Stack (V4)
- **Infra**: Multi-L3 Rollups (Arbitrum Orbit)
- **Cross-Project**: REP-Bridges (Optimism↔Solana)
- **Agents**: MetaOrchestrator, BridgeAgent

## **Stadt/Region (500+, 10k€/Monat)**
- **Zweck**: Leipzig Smart City (V3.2)
- **Tiers**: Bürger → Stadtrat (eID KYC)
- **M2M**: Energy Grid (kWh trades)
- **Governance**: REP-DAO + Multisig

## **Multi-City/Meta (1000+, V4)**
- **Zweck**: Berlin-München Grid
- **L3**: Per-City Rollups + Shared Sequencer
- **Meta-Economy**: Cross-REP (50% conversion)

**Quickstart**: See genesis-agent.py + V4 PDF (Layer 11).
